Negative numbers are composite numbers. Every composite number is dull. Natural numbers are fractions. Each even number is not hot. Real numbers are numbers. Negative numbers are hot. Alex is a negative number.
in_context_example1.query: True or false: Alex is hot.

in_context_example2.question: Each crustacean is happy. Every moth is a crustacean. Each ant is not happy. Every moth is floral. Crustaceans are insects. Polly is a crustacean.
in_context_example2.query: True or false: Polly is happy.

in_context_example3.question: Each lepidopteran is a crustacean. Ants are not orange. Each crustacean is an invertebrate. Each crustacean is not dull. Animals are temperate. Each ant is a lepidopteran. Every lepidopteran is not temperate. Stella is a lepidopteran.
in_context_example3.query: True or false: Stella is not temperate.

test_example.question: Butterflies are not transparent. Arthropods are ants. Every lepidopteran is an insect. Spiders are arthropods. Moths are spiders. Each arthropod is not large. Animals are not feisty. Each invertebrate is not luminous. Each ant is a lepidopteran. Every spider is kind. Every butterfly is an invertebrate. Every invertebrate is a moth. Moths are blue. Each ant is earthy. Every lepidopteran is feisty. Rex is a lepidopteran.
test_example.query: True or false: Rex is not feisty.
